dence;\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  }\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  if (value.notes !== undefined) {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    if (typeof value.notes !== \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"string\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\") {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      throw new TypeError(`${field}.notes must be a string.`);\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    }\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    normalized.notes = value.notes.trim();\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  }\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  return normalized;\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nfunction normalizeUniqueStringArray(value, field) {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  if (!Array.isArray(value)) {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    throw new TypeError(`${field} must be an array.`);\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  }\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  return [...new Set(value.map((item) => {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    if (typeof item !== \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"string\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" || !item.trim()) {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      throw new TypeError(`${field} entries must be non-empty strings.`);\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    }\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    return item.trim();\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  }))];\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"exit_code\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}}\\\\\\\\n./spec/KAN-9/runs/20260509T134353Z-25602558081/events.jsonl:22:{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item.completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item_10\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command_execution\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sed -n '1,260p' README.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"aggregated_output\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"# The Dark Factory\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nA self-driving Jira → GitHub Actions → Claude Code loop. A Jira ticket\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nbecomes either a reviewable pull request or a Jira-facing answer,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nwithout anyone touching a terminal.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## How it works\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n1. Jira automation fires a `repository_dispatch` of type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n   `jira_manual_button` carrying the issue key (a manual\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n   `workflow_dispatch` is also accepted).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n2. [`.github/workflows/jira-dispatch.yml`](.github/workflows/jira-dispatch.yml)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n   runs [`.github/scripts/jira-dispatch.mjs`](.github/scripts/jira-dispatch.mjs):\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n   fetches the ticket from Jira, prepares `spec/<TICKET-ID>/`, restores\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n   any cached Claude session, runs `anthropics/claude-code-base-action@main`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n   on Opus, then commits, opens (or updates) the PR, and comments back\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n   on Jira.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n3. Routing is by Jira label / type:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n   - label `claude:answer` (or issue type `Question`) → answer mode.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n     Claude writes only inside `spec/<TICKET-ID>/`; `response.md` is\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n     posted as a Jira comment.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n   - label `claude:pr` (or default) → PR mode. Claude makes the\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n     repository changes on `tdf/<ticket-id>` and the workflow opens a\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n     PR.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n4. When the PR merges,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n   [`.github/workflows/jira-pr-merged.yml`](.github/workflows/jira-pr-merged.yml)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n   transitions the Jira ticket to Done and deletes the head branch.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nSession continuity across runs comes from `actions/cache`-ing\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n`~/.claude/projects/` (key prefix `tdf-claude-<KEY>-`) plus replaying\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n`spec/<TICKET-ID>/state.json` and `transcript.md` so progress survives\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ncache eviction.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Per-ticket artefacts\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nspec/<TICKET-ID>/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  spec.md         ticket snapshot (refreshed each run)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  plan.md         implementation plan (Claude owns this)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  response.md     Jira-facing summary or answer\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  state.json      last_session_id, run_count, kind, conclusion\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  transcript.md   one section per run\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  runs/<ts>-<id>/ per-run prompt + execution copies\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Repo layout\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n| Path | Purpose |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n|---|---|\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n| [`.github/workflows/`](.github/workflows) | The three live workflows (dispatch, PR-merged finalize, POC session). |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n| [`.github/scripts/jira-dispatch.mjs`](.github/scripts/jira-dispatch.mjs) | Jira ↔ GitHub glue: ticket fetch, state, PR open/update, Jira comment, status transitions. |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n| [`CLAUDE.md`](CLAUDE.md) | Operating contract for Claude when invoked by the dispatch flow. |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n| [`docs/workflows.md`](docs/workflows.md) | High-level overview of the workflows with diagrams. |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n| [`github_actions_claude_spec.md`](github_actions_claude_spec.md) | Authoritative spec for running Claude Code from GitHub Actions with cross-run session continuity. Includes validated POC and gotchas. |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n| [`spec/<TICKET-ID>/`](spec) | Per-ticket artefacts (see above). |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n| [`temp/`](temp) | POC artefacts (`temp/poc/`) and historical research (`temp/progress_plan.md`). Kept as history; not part of production. |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n| [`two-pizzas.html`](two-pizzas.html) | Self-contained HTML deliverable from TDS-9. Open directly in a browser. |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Required GitHub secrets\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n| Secret | Used for |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n|---|---|\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n| `CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN` | Auth for `anthropics/claude-code-base-action`. |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n| `JIRA_BASE_URL`, `JIRA_EMAIL`, `JIRA_API_TOKEN` | Jira REST API for ticket fetch, comment, status transitions. |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n| `GH_PR_TOKEN` | PAT with `contents: write` + `pull-requests: write` so the workflow can push to `tdf/*` branches and open PRs against branch-protected `main`. |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Triggering manually\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nFrom a GitHub-side workflow run:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ngh workflow run jira-dispatch.yml -f issue_key=TDS-14\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nOr replicate the Jira automation:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ngh api repos/NurMind-com/The_Dark_Factory/dispatches \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  -f event_type=jira_manual_button \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  -f 'client_payload[issue_key]=TDS-14'\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## See also\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- [`CLAUDE.md`](CLAUDE.md) — what the agent does on each run.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- [`docs/workflows.md`](docs/workflows.md) — system view + diagrams.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- [`github_actions_claude_spec.md`](github_actions_claude_spec.md) —\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  end-to-end spec, cache strategy, gotchas, validated POC.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"exit_code\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}}\\\\\\\\n./spec/KAN-9/runs/20260509T134353Z-25602558081/events.jsonl:25:{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item.started\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item_12\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command_execution\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sed -n '1,260p' test/shopping-profile.test.mjs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"aggregated_output\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\